summary: This is an email chain from May 28, 2021, regarding the coordination of receiving a new file for the Ghislaine Maxwell case from the FBI via the USAfx system. The email involves personnel from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) and the FBI.

persons.name: Comey
persons.context: Appears as the sender of the initial email requesting coordination to receive a new file for the Maxwell case from the FBI via USAfx.

events.title: Coordination for Maxwell case file transfer
events.description: An email chain coordinates the receipt of a new file for the Ghislaine Maxwell case from the FBI to the U.S. Attorney's Office via the USAfx system.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain dated May 28, 2021, concerning the Ghislaine Maxwell case.
The FBI has a new file for the Maxwell case that needs to be sent to the U.S. Attorney's Office (USANYS).
The transfer is to be coordinated using the USAfx system.
The email shows internal procedural coordination between the FBI and the U.S. Attorney's Office.
Multiple individuals are involved but most names and email addresses are redacted in the provided text.
